Hey everyone, I'm dynamically adding subnavigation to a page based on whether that page has sibling pages under it's menu parent node. How can I check this to have the HubSpot decide whether to render the subnav or not. Here's what I tried. It's still rendering the subnav even when it's empty. Thanks!

```{% set menu_main = 9017734495 %}
{% set node = menu(menu_main) %}
{% for branch in node.children %}
{% if branch.activeBranch == True %}
&lt;!-- Start Sub Nav--&gt;
&lt;nav class="sub_nav"&gt;
	&lt;div class="contain"&gt;
		{% for child in node.children %}
		  {% if child.activeBranch == True %}
		  &lt;h6 class="parent"&gt;{{ child.label }}&lt;/h6&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
				{% for child in child.children %}
			    &lt;li {% if child.activeNode == True %} class="active" {% else %} {% endif %}&gt;&lt;a href="{{ child.url }}"&gt;{{ child.label }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
				{% endfor %}
			{% endif %}
		{% endfor %}
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;a href="#" class="btn cta"&gt;Free Session&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;a href="#" class="sub_trigger"&gt;&lt;img src="https://cdn2.HubSpot.net/hubfs/411995/emyth.com-files/svg/icons/down_arrow.svg" alt="Open"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;!-- End Sub Nav --&gt;
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}```
